  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;üïí&lt;/span&gt;¬†&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180139/rss" title="croner.56k.guru" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Croner 10.0: Cron-Style Triggers and Evaluation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî Trigger functions on any cron schedule using &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180140/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;cron syntax.&lt;/a&gt; It can also evaluate cron expressions to give you a list of upcoming times. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180141/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;v10.0&lt;/a&gt; brings full OCPS (Open Cron Pattern Specification) 1.4 compliance and even more scheduling¬†options.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Hexagon &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;üóìÔ∏è&lt;/span&gt;¬†&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180142/rss" title="dayflow-js.github.io" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;DayFlow: A Full Calendar Component for React&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî A React-only feature-rich calendar component with drag-and-drop, multiple views, and all the usual GCal-style richness. Its infinite scrolling feature is nifty. &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180143/rss" style=" color: #3366aa;   "&gt;GitHub¬†repo.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;DayFlow Contributors &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1em; color: #000;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180144/rss" title="tsonic.org" style=" color: #3366aa;    font-size: 1.05em;"&gt;Tsonic: A TypeScript to C# Transpiler&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ‚Äî The idea is for creating native executables that run on .NET. I‚Äôve not tested it as I‚Äôm not in that ecosystem but it‚Äôs an interesting¬†idea.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Jeswin &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.48em;  padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px;  padding-left: 15px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180145/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;EmbedPDF 2.4&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Framework-agnostic JavaScript PDF viewer. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180146/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Demo.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180147/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;JavaScriptKit v0.40&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Swift framework for interacting with JS via¬†WASM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180148/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;StackBlur.js 3.0&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Long-standing Gaussian blur library; now using¬†ESM.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180149/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Knip 5.83&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Finds and fixes unused files, dependencies and¬†exports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÑ &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180150/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;jsPDF 4.1&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Generate PDFs directly in JavaScript. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180151/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Demo.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180152/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;qrcode.vue 3.8&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Vue.js component to generate QR¬†codes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180153/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;focus-trap 8.0&lt;/a&gt; ‚Äì Trap focus within a DOM node. (&lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/180154/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;Demo.&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
