&lt;p&gt;üìä &lt;em&gt;HTTP Archive&lt;/em&gt; has released its &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179497/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;latest &lt;em&gt;Web Almanac&lt;/em&gt; for 2025&lt;/a&gt; packed with raw stats, trends, and observations about the state of the Web over the past year, covering areas like &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179498/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;WebAssembly&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179499/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;performance&lt;/a&gt;, and ever-increasing &lt;a href="https://javascriptweekly.com/link/179500/rss" style=" color: #3366aa; font-weight: 500 !important;   "&gt;page¬†weight&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
